The paper deals with the performance of Rate-Splitting (RS) based on Tomlinson-Harashima Precoding (THP) in a multiple-antenna broadcast channel with perfect and imperfect Channel State Information at the Transmitter (CSIT). This topic falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT), Communication (cs.COMM), and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the signal-to-interference-plus-noise (SINR) ratio and the sum rates associated with these schemes, which are related to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories.
